	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Montegue</b><br /><i>Is that just a theory, or can you show that in history?<br />
<br />
It strikes me that a Company without any controll would severely abuse it's workers, would become a monopoly, and would basically take over the world. I may be crazy, but two of those three things have happened, and the third is aroudn the proverbial corner.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />
That happened in the Deep South when Cotton was King. The  cotton mills were  small fifedoms ruled by cotton barons. They owned the housing, the store and up to and including the church you attended. <br />
You were required to have  1 person working for every occupied room of a house. They also owned the  entertainment outlets you used. The ball field? Owned by the  mill owner. The school? Also owned by the mill owner.<br />
 <br />
<a href="http://www.owdna.org/history15.htm" target="_blank"> Click here </a> if you want an eye opening  history lesson of the deep South.</p>
	
	
	
