	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Kross -<br />
 <br />
Given the history of business, and modern Corporate America, I doubt the theory would prove true. Even if that theory panned out to be the utopian economy you describe, I doubt such a thing would have any prayer of success in the current climate. <br />
 <br />
Companies would go back to exploiting thier workers. they would do away with the 5 day work week. Overtime would go away. Men and women would once again literally work themselves to death. They would cut healthcare costs. They would bring back all the things that we have protected the worker from, because it would mean the most money for the fat cats at the top. <br />
 <br />
Kross, has this model you present worked in the past? Is the deep south a place where it went bad or good? (I didnt read the posted article)</p>
	
	
	
